                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13911393" author="chetanm" created="Tue, 25 Feb 2014 08:42:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is that required. Can we keep it monotonic increasing and avoid decrementing it as caching logic depends on this value change for keep state consistent&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13911407" author="mreutegg" created="Tue, 25 Feb 2014 09:04:40 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Can we keep it monotonic increasing and avoid decrementing&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;yes, this is what I want to fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13911411" author="chetanm" created="Tue, 25 Feb 2014 09:13:09 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;yes, this is what I want to fix.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Aah my fault I read bug description as &lt;em&gt;document&lt;/em&gt; that _modCount is not monotonic increasing !!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13911433" author="mreutegg" created="Tue, 25 Feb 2014 09:52:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Turns out the problem wasn&apos;t too severe. &lt;tt&gt;Commit.rollback()&lt;/tt&gt; did try to apply a reverse UpdateOp with a _modCount decrement, but the MongoDocumentStore implementation overwrites it with an increment. I changed the implementation anyway, because it was confusing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1571634&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1571634&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13930156" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Tue, 11 Mar 2014 09:51:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;bulk close for the 0.18 release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
